  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mbam - Upper Sanaga Valley Integrated Sheep/Goat Project (Central Province)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Farmers, Women</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will support 450 resource-limited farm families over five years in the central Cameroon regions of Mbam and Inoubou. People in this area face food insecurity, low income, and gender inequities. To assist, 150 families will receive 750 sheep and goats from previous projects, with a total of 5 per family. These original families will then pass-on 1,500 sheep and goats to another 300 farm families. In addition to the animals, families will be trained on Heifer&#x2019;s 12 Cornerstones, group development and management, improved animal and crop husbandry and enterprise development. The project will also train families on prevention of HIV/AIDS, and will facilitate access to voluntary counseling and testing. Project staff will also mainstream gender equity in the implementation of project activities. At least 60 percent of project participants will be women and disadvantaged persons.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Train farmers on Heifer&#x2019;s 12 cornerstones, group development and management, improved animal and crop husbandry, integrated crop-livestock techniques, market gardening, post-harvest management and enterprise development. Purchase and place sheep/goats, crop seeds and other farm inputs. Sensitize families on prevention of HIV and AIDS and facilitate access to voluntary counseling and testing.</narrative>
  </description>
